14 TO CELEBRATE AND RECOGNIZE MARCH 21,
15 2025, AS WORLD DOWN SYNDROME DAY IN THE
16 STATE OF ARKANSAS.
17
18 WHEREAS, Down Syndrome is a naturally occurring chromosomal arrangement
19 that has always been a part of the human condition, exists in all regions
20 across the globe, and commonly results in variable effects on learning
21 styles, physical characteristics, or health; and
22
23 WHEREAS, adequate access to health care, early intervention programs,
24 and inclusive education are vital to the growth and development of
25 individuals with Down Syndrome; and
26
27 WHEREAS, it is imperative that all remember the inherent dignity,
28 worth, and valuable contributions of persons with intellectual disabilities
29 and the importance of each person's autonomy and independence; and
30
31 WHEREAS, the date for World Down Syndrome Day is the twenty-first day
32 of the third month, selected to signify the uniqueness of the triplication of
33 the twenty-first chromosome that causes Down Syndrome; and
34
35 WHEREAS, Down Syndrome is a genetic disorder affecting one (1) in over
36 seven hundred (700) babies or approximately six thousand (6,000) births per
